{"id": "duc04-testb-40:2#7", "contents": "Clinton's speech highlighted the old-style regional military threat posed by North Korea, a subject that has consumed much of his meetings with President Kim Dae-jung of South Korea. He compared North Korea to Iraq, citing its chemical and biological weapons as a major concern. Clinton restated his support for Kim's policy of engagement with North Korea, noting \"some hopeful signs\" to justify it, including talks between the American military command in Korea and the North Korean military to prevent problems along the demilitarized zone."}
